track_notes: This track is a 9-mile hike beginning at the trailhead in Saguaro National Park.  After 7 miles you reach Juniper Basin Campground, then the final 2 miles to the Summit.  Trail is overgrown in places and you need to look for rock cairns in some of the more rocky parts to stay on trail.  There are some steep sections and the very final summit requires a few steps of Class 3 rock climbing but its very achievable.
